# CODEOWNERS — ActraDeck
#
# Purpose: route review of the security/correctness CHOKE POINTS to a maintainer.
# These paths carry the invariants INV-REDACTION / INV-APPROVAL / INV-EVENT-ORDER /
# INV-STALLED and the auth/token surface. They are intentionally NOT "good first issue"
# territory — see CONTRIBUTING.md ("Where to start" vs "Security-sensitive areas").
#
# There is deliberately NO global owner: everything NOT listed below — docs, demo
# fixtures, the diagnostics scripts, and UI copy / i18n under apps/webui — stays open
# and does not require a maintainer's review. That is where newcomers should start.
#
# Note: CODEOWNERS only AUTO-REQUESTS the listed reviewer. To make it blocking, enable
# "Require review from Code Owners" in the branch-protection rules for `main`.
# Replace @actradeck/maintainers if the maintainer handle / team changes.

# --- Local sidecar: highest-risk surface ---------------------------------------------
# Secret redactor (INV-REDACTION), approval bridge/allowlist/persistence (INV-APPROVAL),
# stdout/stderr + git-diff collectors, append-only log. The whole src tree is owned
# because a leak can originate anywhere a collector or the redact choke point changes.
/apps/sidecar/src/                 @actradeck/maintainers

# --- Canonical event contracts & projection (INV-EVENT-ORDER / INV-STALLED) ----------
# Normalized event model, redaction-kind enum, and the projection/derivation are T1
# (source of truth). Changes here ripple across the whole pipeline.
/packages/event-model/             @actradeck/maintainers
/packages/projection/              @actradeck/maintainers

# --- Backend: event store + state engine + realtime auth ------------------------------
# Ingestion, idempotency/ordering, state derivation, and the realtime token boundary.
/apps/backend/src/                 @actradeck/maintainers

# --- Web UI BFF / realtime transport: token relay + SSRF surface ----------------------
# The custom server and the server/realtime layer relay REALTIME_TOKEN to the backend
# (never to the browser) and proxy WS/replay — this is the token-isolation / SSRF
# boundary (transitive reach, cf. INV token-isolation tests). NOT good-first territory.
# The UI *copy* layer (apps/webui/src/ui/, i18n) is intentionally left open below.
/apps/webui/server.ts              @actradeck/maintainers
/apps/webui/src/server/            @actradeck/maintainers
/apps/webui/src/realtime/          @actradeck/maintainers

# --- Invariant tests must not be weakened without review ------------------------------
/apps/**/test/inv-*.test.ts        @actradeck/maintainers
/packages/**/test/inv-*.test.ts    @actradeck/maintainers

# --- Security policy, threat model, CI, and this file ---------------------------------
/SECURITY.md                       @actradeck/maintainers
/.github/workflows/                @actradeck/maintainers
/.github/CODEOWNERS                @actradeck/maintainers
